oc:kn_1c9c7ebb a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Throughout the entire research document" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not produce merely descriptive summaries — every section must contain substantive analysis, specific examples, quantitative data, and cited sources. Avoid generic statements." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Descriptive filler degrades the report to marketing material quality; institutional clients pay for analytical insight they cannot get elsewhere" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_5ce69827 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing the Management Team section" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Management bios must be 300-400 words per executive for 3-4 key executives (CEO and CFO always required, plus 2 additional C-suite). Each bio must cover current role, prior experience, key accomplishments, and education." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Management quality is a primary factor in institutional investment decisions; insufficient detail prevents assessment of leadership capability" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_65a5c312 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "During competitive analysis and risk assessment phases" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Must analyze 5-10 specific competitors including both direct and indirect competitors, and identify 8-12 distinct risks across all four categories (company-specific, industry/market, financial, macroeconomic) with 50-100 word descriptions each" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Incomplete competitive or risk coverage undermines the credibility of the research and leaves blind spots for investment decisions" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_a95ec3cb a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PostFlightValidation ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After completing the research document" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Verify: total word count reaches 6,000-8,000 words, all 9 required sections present with target word counts, analysis is substantive (not just descriptive), specific examples and data included, all sources cited, and file saved as [Company]_Research_Document_[Date].md" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Systematic validation ensures institutional-quality output before downstream tasks consume the document" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_bc975b59 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When structuring and writing the document" ;
    oc:directiveContent "The research document serves as both a standalone analysis and foundational input for downstream tasks: Task 2 (Financial Modeling), Task 4 (Chart Generation), and Task 5 (Report Assembly where Company 101 sections are copied verbatim)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Content reuse across the initiation workflow requires clean section boundaries and self-contained analysis that can be extracted independently" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_cd09f87f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before beginning Task 1 research" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Verify company name or ticker symbol is available before starting. No other prerequisites exist — this task is fully independent." ;
    oc:hasRationale "This is the first task in the initiating-coverage workflow and has no dependencies on prior tasks" ;
    oc:severityLevel "LOW" .

oc:kn_f323f529 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing the final company research document" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Each section must meet minimum word count targets: Company Overview (800-1,200), Company History (800-1,200), Management Team (1,000-1,400), Products & Services (700-1,000), Customers & GTM (500-700), Industry Overview (800-1,200), Competitive Landscape (700-1,000), Market Opportunity (500-700), Risk Assessment (600-900). Total must reach 6,000-8,000 words." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Institutional-quality research reports require sufficient depth per section to provide actionable intelligence for portfolio managers and analysts" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_f378e899 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When beginning company research" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Start research with the company website and SEC filings (10-K, 10-Q, DEF 14A, 8-K), then expand to earnings transcripts and investor presentations, and finally secondary sources (competitor filings, industry reports, news)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Primary sources provide the most reliable and comprehensive foundation; secondary sources add context but should not drive the narrative" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

